With this concept in mind, Women As Leaders covered some tips to help sustain your marriage. Remember this is solely from personal experience and suggested for both men and women to address. Not every tip will work for every couple but start by trying a few out.

Tip #1

Love without the expectation that your partner would love you back. We are all created differently and do not love the same way. Make sure you give more than take. Often people say what I call the five “L” words that are detrimental towards a marriage; Lies, Laziness, Lack of Loyalty, and Lack of Longevity and Lack of Loyalty. If these four items are not in your marriage then our relationship can continue to prosper.

Tip #2

Love with the purpose of leaving a legacy. Put your energy into developing legacy concepts. Find a way to bless and serve others. A marriage can continue for a lifetime with this intention. Be intentional in building your family legacy. Revisit as time goes by and stay consistent in the things that will build your legacy.

“Love one another as I have loved you.” -John 15:12
